quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,38,"And he builds{1}the ship, and whenever some chiefs from among his people passed by him, they would mock him. He said, “If you mock us, surely we mock you just as you mock;",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense, which serves to create a vivid portrait of past events.
  11,39,"then you will come to know upon whom shall come a punishment that disgraces him, and upon whom a perpetual punishment shall fall.”"
  11,40,"Until, when Our command came and the oven overflowed{1}, We said, “Carry in it, ofeach kind, a male and female couple{2}, and your family—except those against whom the sentence has already been passed—and those who have attained faith.” But none attained faith with him except a few.",footnotes:1:[As a sign to embark the ship.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs read it as:” Carry in it, of each female and male kind, one couple,”Carry in it, of each female and male kind, one couple,”]
  11,41,"And he said, “Embark in it. In the name of Allah shall be its sailing{1}and its anchorage. My Lord is most surely Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy.”",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Abu Amr and Warsh read it as: “In the name of Allah who causes it to sail and who causes it to anchor.”
  11,42,"And so it sails<sup>b </sup>with them amidst waves like mountains. And Noah called to his son who had kept away, “O my child! Embark with us and do not be with the deniers.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense, which serves to create a vivid portrait of past events.
  11,43,"He said, “I will take shelter on a mountain which can safeguard me from the water.” He said, “There is no safeguard from Allah’s command today, except for the one on whom He has bestowed mercy.” And the waves surged between them, and he became of the drowned."
  11,44,"And it was said, “O land, swallow your waters,” and “O sky, clear up.” And the waters receded, and the matter was concluded, and it settled on<i>(mount) </i>Judei, and it was said: “Away with the unjust people.”"
  11,45,"And Noah called to his Lord and said, “O My Lord, my son is indeed of my family, and Your promise is indeed the truth, and You are the Wisest of all judges.”"
